[{"id":"VH922837","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a map of the Earth with areas indicated for the following three categories: geothermal, petroleum wells, and coal deposits. Petroleum wells are located along the southern coast of Alaska. A geothermal area is located in Iceland. Geothermal areas are also located in the western United States, in the rocky mountain region. Petroleum wells and coal deposits are located in the southern United States, in and around Texas. Coal deposits are located in southeastern United States, in the Appalachian mountain region.\" height=\"248\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH922837.g01.png\" width=\"465\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following geologic profiles would most likely be found at the circled region in the figure?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH922837_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a layer of disconformity, consisting of metamorphic rock to the left of igneous rock.\" height=\"76\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH922837.g09.png\" width=\"200\"></span></p>\n","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents four layers of the Earth. Beginning at the bottom and moving upward, the layers of Earth are: Igneous Rock, Sedimentary Rock, Peat with fossilized plants, and Peat with fossilized leaves.\" height=\"151\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH922837.g11.png\" width=\"200\"></span></p>\n","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents four layers of the Earth. Beginning at the bottom and moving upward, the layers of Earth are: igneous rock, silt, sandstone with fossilized shells, and clay.\" height=\"153\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH922837.g05.png\" width=\"200\"></span></p>\n","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents 4 layers of the Earth. Beginning at the bottom and moving upwards, the first three layers demonstrate angular unconformity and consist of igneous rock, magma, and igneous rock. The top layer consists of sedimentary rock.\" height=\"186\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH922837.g10.png\" width=\"200\"></span></p>\n"],"answer":1}]